---
import '../styles/globals.css';
import BrandingLogo from '../components/BrandingLogo.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'June 2025';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon-32.png" />
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
  <title>Terms & Conditions – Zyppi</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Read Zyppi's Terms and Conditions governing the use of our ride-booking app and platform in India." />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://zyppi.in/term-condition" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#673AB7" />
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-900 antialiased">

  <!-- NAV -->
  <header class="sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-white/10 bg-[hsl(243_75%_22%)] shadow-lg">
    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-4xl items-center justify-between px-4 py-4 sm:px-6">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
        <div class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-white p-1.5">
          <img src="/logo.png" alt="Zyppi logo" class="h-6 w-6 object-contain" data-branding-logo />
        </div>
        <span class="text-xl font-bold tracking-wide text-white">ZYPPI</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/" class="text-sm text-white/70 hover:text-white transition-colors">← Back to Home</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-indigo-600 mb-2">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated} &nbsp;·&nbsp; Please read carefully before using Zyppi.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-10 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <p class="text-base">
          These Terms & Conditions ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the Zyppi mobile application and the website <strong>zyppi.in</strong> (collectively, the "Platform"), operated by Zyppi ("Company", "we", "our" or "us"). By downloading, installing or using the Platform, you ("User", "Rider", "Driver" or "Vehicle Owner") agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Eligibility</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>You must be at least <strong>18 years of age</strong> to use the Platform.</li>
          <li>Drivers and vehicle owners must hold a valid driving licence and vehicle registration as required by Indian law.</li>
          <li>By using the Platform you represent and warrant that all information you provide is accurate and that you have the legal capacity to enter into this agreement.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Platform Services</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">Zyppi provides a technology platform that connects:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Riders</strong> seeking transportation or goods-delivery services.</li>
          <li><strong>Drivers and Vehicle Owners</strong> willing to provide those services.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3">
          Zyppi is a technology intermediary and is <strong>not a transportation company</strong>. The actual transport service is provided by independent drivers and vehicle owners. We do not guarantee the availability of any service at any time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. User Accounts</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials.</li>
          <li>You must notify us immediately at <a href="mailto:admin@zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">admin@zyppi.in</a> if you suspect unauthorised access to your account.</li>
          <li>Each mobile number may be associated with only one account. Creating multiple accounts to abuse promotions is prohibited.</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Bookings & Cancellations</h2>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">4.1 For Riders</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>A booking is confirmed only after a driver accepts your request.</li>
          <li>You may cancel a booking before the driver arrives. Repeated cancellations may result in temporary restriction of your booking ability.</li>
          <li>Cancellation fees may apply if you cancel after a driver has been assigned and has travelled towards your pickup location.</li>
          <li>No-shows (rider absent at pickup after driver arrival) may attract a fee and be counted against your account.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">4.2 For Drivers</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>Accepting a booking creates a binding obligation to complete the trip unless an emergency prevents it.</li>
          <li>Repeated cancellations after acceptance may result in lower trip priority or account suspension.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Fares & Payments</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>Fares are calculated based on base price, per-km rate, time, and applicable surcharges displayed before booking confirmation.</li>
          <li>Accepted payment methods include UPI, debit/credit card, net banking and cash (where enabled).</li>
          <li>All payments are processed through PCI-DSS compliant third-party payment gateways. Zyppi does not store full card details.</li>
          <li>Promo codes and discounts are subject to their individual terms and cannot be combined unless explicitly stated.</li>
          <li>In case of disputes about fare charges, contact us within 48 hours of the trip. We may review trip data to resolve the dispute.</li>
          <li>GST and other applicable taxes are included in the displayed fare.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">6. Driver & Vehicle Owner Terms</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>Drivers and vehicle owners must complete KYC verification and upload all required documents before being activated on the Platform.</li>
          <li>All documents (driving licence, RC, insurance, permit) must be valid and kept up to date. Operating with expired documents may result in immediate deactivation.</li>
          <li>Drivers must maintain a minimum rating and completion rate as communicated in the app. Persistent underperformance may result in deactivation.</li>
          <li>Drivers are independent contractors, not employees of Zyppi. You are responsible for your own taxes, insurance and compliance with applicable law.</li>
          <li>Earnings are calculated based on completed trips and credited to your registered bank account or UPI ID per the payout schedule communicated in the app.</li>
          <li>Zyppi reserves the right to deactivate a driver or vehicle at any time for safety, compliance or policy violations.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">7. Conduct & Prohibited Activities</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">You agree <strong>not</strong> to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>Use the Platform for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable law.</li>
          <li>Harass, threaten, abuse or discriminate against other users, drivers or Zyppi staff.</li>
          <li>Provide false information during registration or KYC.</li>
          <li>Manipulate the rating system or offer incentives for positive reviews.</li>
          <li>Circumvent or attempt to circumvent fare calculation or payment systems.</li>
          <li>Use the Platform to solicit cash trips outside the app to avoid platform fees.</li>
          <li>Carry or transport prohibited or illegal goods.</li>
          <li>Reproduce, modify, distribute or create derivative works of the Platform without our express written permission.</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to our systems, networks or user accounts.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3">Violation of these prohibitions may result in immediate account termination and legal action.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">8. Ratings & Reviews</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          After each completed trip, both riders and drivers may rate each other. Ratings are used to maintain service quality. Zyppi reserves the right to remove ratings that violate our content guidelines or are determined to be fraudulent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">9. Safety</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>Riders should verify the vehicle registration number and driver photo before boarding.</li>
          <li>In an emergency, use the SOS feature in the app or call 112.</li>
          <li>Drivers must not drive under the influence of alcohol or controlled substances.</li>
          <li>Wearing seatbelts is mandatory for all occupants where applicable.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>Zyppi acts as a technology intermediary and is not liable for the actions, omissions or conduct of drivers, vehicle owners or riders.</li>
          <li>We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential or punitive damages arising from your use of the Platform.</li>
          <li>Our total liability to you for any claim shall not exceed the amount paid by you for the specific transaction giving rise to the claim.</li>
          <li>We do not warrant that the Platform will be error-free, uninterrupted or free of viruses or other harmful components.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">11. Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          You agree to indemnify, defend and hold harmless Zyppi and its officers, directors, employees and agents from any claims, liabilities, damages, losses and expenses (including legal fees) arising out of or related to your use of the Platform, your violation of these Terms, or your violation of any rights of a third party.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">12. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          All content, trademarks, logos, and technology on the Platform are the exclusive property of Zyppi or its licensors. You are granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to use the Platform for personal, non-commercial purposes. Nothing in these Terms transfers any intellectual property rights to you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">13. Termination</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          We may suspend or terminate your access to the Platform at any time, without prior notice, for conduct that we believe violates these Terms or is harmful to other users, Zyppi, or third parties. You may close your account at any time by contacting support. Termination does not relieve you of any obligations (including pending payments) incurred prior to termination.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">14. Governing Law & Dispute Resolution</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with these Terms shall first be attempted to be resolved through good-faith negotiation. If unresolved within 30 days, disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in India.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">15. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          We reserve the right to update these Terms at any time. We will notify you of material changes via the app or email. Your continued use of the Platform after the effective date of changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms. If you do not agree to any changes, you must stop using the Platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">16. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">For any questions about these Terms, please contact:</p>
        <div class="mt-3 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-100 px-5 py-4 text-sm space-y-1">
          <p><strong>Zyppi — Legal & Compliance</strong></p>
          <p>Email &amp; Support: <a href="mailto:admin@zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">admin@zyppi.in</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">https://zyppi.in</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <footer class="bg-gray-900 py-8 mt-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 flex flex-col items-center gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:justify-between">
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">© {new Date().getFullYear()} Zyppi. All rights reserved.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 text-xs text-gray-500">
        <a href="/privacy-policy" class="hover:text-gray-400 transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>
        <a href="/term-condition" class="text-indigo-400">Terms & Conditions</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <BrandingLogo />
</body>
</html>
